# Chamber
  `entered_chamber := true`
  > The bell chamber is round, dry, and impossibly deep beneath the ruined tower.
  > A cracked silver bell hangs from three chains over a black pool. The chains vanish into the ceiling without hooks or beams.
  > Sound behaves strangely here. Your breath arrives late, and your footsteps seem embarrassed to have interrupted.
  > `chalk_circle` A chalk ring glows faintly at the pool's edge, thin and steady as moonlight trapped under ice.
  + -> [Inspect the bell](#.Bell)
  + -> [Study the pool](#.Pool)
  + -> [Climb back to the courtyard](/ruins.saga#Courtyard)

## Bell
  > The bell has no tongue. Its inner curve is scratched with names you almost recognize.
  > Some names are written in old village script, some in careful modern hands, and one seems to rearrange itself when you blink.
  > `bronze_tongue` The bronze tongue hums softly in your pack. It is not a sound so much as a pressure behind your eyes.
  + `bronze_tongue` -> [Fit the bronze tongue into place](#.Restore)
  + -> [Touch the scratched names](#.Names)
  + -> [Step away](#Chamber)

### Restore
  `bell_restored := true`
  > The bronze tongue rises from your hand and locks itself inside the bell.
  > The chamber tightens around the gesture. Even the black pool seems to hold its surface still.
  + `trust_blue_scarf` *-> [Ring the bell](#..TrueRing)
  + -> [Ring the bell anyway](#..FalseRing)
  + -> [Wait and listen](#..Names)

### TrueRing
  `bell_rang_true := true`
  > The bell rings without sound. The black pool becomes a sky full of dawn.
  > Light pours upward, warm and impossible, carrying the smell of wet grass and banked hearth fires.
  + -> [Continue](/ending.saga#Dawn)

### FalseRing
  `bell_rang_false := true`
  > The bell screams. Every chain in the chamber snaps tight, then slackens.
  > The sound has no volume, only weight. It drops through you and keeps falling.
  + -> [Continue](/ending.saga#Return)

### Names
  `name_glimpse = rand(3)`
  > Your name is there, but the letters keep changing order.
  > Around it are other names: some familiar, some impossible, some written with strokes too deep to have been made by any hand.
  - `name_glimpse == 0` *-> [Continue](#.HiddenName)
  - -> [Continue](#..)

#### HiddenName
  `saw_hidden_name := true`
  > For one breath, the letters spell a name that is not yours, but answers when you think it.
  > It settles behind your ribs like a second heartbeat, then goes quiet.
  + -> [Continue](#..)

## Pool
  > The pool reflects the chamber as it was: whole, full of candlelight, crowded with silent villagers.
  > Their faces are turned upward toward the bell. None of them move until you do.
  > `pool_offering` A stranger in the reflection turns your coin over in their fingers and smiles at a joke you have not heard yet.
  + `coin >= 1` -> [Drop a coin into the pool](#.Offering)
  + `found_chalk` -> [Draw a chalk circle at the pool's edge](#.Circle)
  + -> [Return to the bell](#..Bell)

### Offering
  `coin := coin - 1`
  `pool_offering := true`
  > The coin falls upward through the reflection and lands in someone else's palm.
  > For a moment, the reflected crowd parts around the stranger as if they have been waiting for payment.
  + -> [Continue](#..)

### Circle
  `chalk_circle := true`
  > The chalk line closes itself into a perfect ring. The pool grows still.
  > The reflected villagers lower their eyes. Whatever they expected, the circle has made them reconsider.
  + -> [Continue](#..)
